  <h3 id="Gumroads-fees-are-simple--EFxXf">Gumroad's fees are progressive</h3>
  <p>Gumroad uses progressive pricing that rewards growth. You only pay each rate on the sales within that tier, plus $0.50 per transaction. Tiers reset at the start of every month:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>30%</strong> on your first $100/month in sales</li>
    <li><strong>12.5%</strong> on sales from $100 to $1,000/month</li>
    <li><strong>8.5%</strong> on sales from $1,000 to $5,000/month</li>
    <li><strong>4.9%</strong> on sales above $5,000/month</li>
  </ul>
  <p>These fees include <a href="https://gumroad.com/pricing">sales tax</a> handling. Credit card processing (2.9% + $0.30) and <a href="https://www.paypal.com/us/webapps/mpp/merchant-fees" target="_blank">PayPal fees</a> are separate.</p>
  <p>Sales made through Gumroad's marketplace (Discover) are subject to a flat 30% fee, which includes all processing fees.</p>
  <p>There are no monthly payments or other hidden charges.</p>
  <p>If you wish to see the exact fees taken out on every sale, you can <a href="74-the-analytics-dashboard#sales-csv">export a CSV of your sales</a>, giving a full breakdown of every sale.</p>
  <h3 id="Affiliates-sW9pK">Affiliates</h3>
  <p>For <a href="333-affiliates-on-gumroad">affiliates</a>, fees on affiliate purchases are split between the affiliate and the creator proportional to the affiliate's commission. For example, if an affiliate's commission is 30%, they'll be responsible for 30% of the fees on the purchase.</p>
  <h3 id="Refunds-aSEwt">Refunds</h3>
  <p>We don't refund any fees when processing refunds. Learn more about refunds <a href="https://gumroad.com/help/article/47-how-to-refund-a-customer">here</a>.</p>
